      "writtenOn": "2021-06-28T08:00:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sure.\nActually, I came up with such approach while working on this CL https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromiumos/platform/tast-tests/+/2987941 (it chains the current CL). I was getting a lot of closers there. So instead of working with two context objects (the parent one for defer blocks and the shortened child for rest of the program) I wrote this utility.\n\n\nI need it inside (local/bundles/cros). So instead of restricting its usage to only the local tests, I put it on tast. How about putting it into tast/common/utils package (inside tast-tests)?",
      "parentUuid": "927f79ba_5a7d39e6",
      "revId": "346babcd98fef07641ba63c13935e051072b17cb",
